<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,671,1657]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,627,1470,1496]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Australasian distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[645,733,1471,1497]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 20" captionStartId="13.[264,382,1535,1559]" captionTargetBox="[303,1287,325,1511]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[291,1295,316,1521]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 20. Distribution maps of Drosophila montium subgroup species in the Australasian Region. (14) Drosophila dominicana. (15) Drosophila montium subgroup species undissected and unclassified. (16) Drosophila kikkawai. (17) Drosophila sp. cf. jambulina. (18) Drosophila bunnanda (19) Drosophila birchii. (20) Drosophila serrata." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174256/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[701,733,1471,1497]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[755,984,1471,1497]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
(Madang, Goroka and Wau) and Queensland. Reported only from urban habitats in 
<collectingCountry box="[917,1028,1511,1537]" name="Australia" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Australia</collectingCountry>
. Widespread outside this region, occurring throughout southeast Asia, across Oceania and in the Neotropical Region (Baimai 
<number box="[462,524,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1980.0">1980</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Baimai" box="[539,881,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="17" refString="Baimai, V. &amp; Chumchong, C. (1980) Karyotype variation and geographic distribution of the three sibling species of the Drosophila kikkawai complex. Genetica, 54, 113 - 120." type="journal article" year="1980">
Baimai &amp; Chumchong 
<number box="[819,881,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Bock 
<number box="[967,1029,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1977.0">1977</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Carson" box="[1044,1317,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" refString="Carson, H. L. &amp; Okada, T. (1983) Drosophilidae from banana traps over an altitudinal transect in Papua New Guinea. II. Frequency of species at eight collecting sites. International Journal of Entomology, 25, 142 - 151." type="journal article" year="1983">
Carson &amp; Okada 
<number box="[1255,1317,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1983.0">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; also see Appendix).
</paragraph>
